For Loop:-
-> number of iterations are known.

class Count{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        for (int i=1;i<=5;i++){
            System.out.println(i);
        }
    }
}

While loop:-
-> Number of iteration are unknown.

class Count{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        int i=1;
        while (i<=5){
            System.out.println(i);
            i++;
        }
    }
}

Do-While loop:-
-> Execute atleast ones.

class Count{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        do {
           System.out.println("Count: " + j);
           j++;
        } while (j <= 5);
    }
}

For-Each loop:-
-> Used to iterate over arrays/collections.

class Numbers{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        int[] numbers = {10, 20, 30, 40};
        for (int num : numbers) {
            System.out.println(num);
        }
    }
}


